-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Thu Aug 28, 2014 06:07AM EDT
-- None



Aug 28 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1000 GMT on Thursday:

** Vivendi <VIV.PA> said it received bids for its GVT Brazilian broadband unit from Telecom Italia <TLIT.MI> and Telefonica <TEF.MC>, and that its supervisory board would examine the offers at a meeting on Thursday. The Telecom Italia offer represents a total enterprise value of 7 billion euros ($9.24 billion), while the Telefonica offer represents a total enterprise value of 7.45 billion euros. [ID:nWEA00ERP]  ** Oak Hill Capital Partners LP, the private equity owner of restaurant and arcade chain Dave & Buster's Inc, is considering raising a smaller fund than its previous $3.8 billion flagship buyout fund, according to people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL5N0QX53L]  ** The state of Western Australia on Thursday said it planned to sell government-owned assets, including part of the Port Hedland shipping terminal, for an estimated A$1 billion to A$2 billion ($1.9 billion) as its resource-heavy economy adjusts to the collapse of a decade-long mining boom. [ID:nL3N0QY1V8]  ** Two Chinese firms are among companies which have approached STATS ChipPAC Ltd <STTS.SI> about acquiring it, the Singapore provider of technology services said on Thursday. STATS ChipPAC, which has a market value of $1.2 billion and is majority owned by state investor Temasek Holdings [TEM.UL], identified Jiangsu Changjiang Electronics Technology Co <600584.SS> and Tianshui Huatian Technology Co <002185.SZ> as possible bidders. [ID:nL3N0QX5Y7]   ** Lear Corp <LEA.N>, a maker of auto seats and electrical power systems, said it would buy automotive leather supplier Eagle Ottawa LLC for $850 million to strengthen its core seating business and boost its luxury seats portfolio. [ID:nL3N0QX56U]  ** Chinese private equity firm Hony Capital will sell a tranche of over $500 million of shares in CSPC Pharmaceutical Group Ltd <1093.HK> for the second time in three months, cashing in on the drugmaker's buoyant stock. Hony is offering 650 million shares in fast-growing CSPC in an indicative range of HK$6.30 to HK$6.45 each, worth up to $535 million, according to a term sheet seen by IFR, a Thomson Reuters publication. [ID:nL3N0QY1M6]  **  Australia's largest buyout firm Pacific Equity Partners said it had sold down its stake in newly-listed credit rating company Veda Group Ltd <VED.AX>, making a A$243 million ($227.42 million) profit on share gains over eight months. PEP sold the stake for A$2.15 per share, or A$580 million. [ID:nL3N0QY21F]  ** India's Adani Enterprises Ltd <ADEL.NS> has agreed to pay A$155 million ($145 million) to Linc Energy <LINC.SI> to buy out the Australian firm's rights to future royalties from Adani's huge but delayed Carmichael coal project, already four years behind schedule. [ID:nL3N0QY18P]  **  Support services group DCC <DCC.L> on Thursday said it had agreed to buy Esso's <ESSF.PA> motorway retail network in France, its biggest ever acquisition, for 84 million pounds ($139.36 million). [ID:nL5N0QY141]  ** Tiger Resources Ltd <TGS.AX> has agreed to buy out the Democratic Republic of Congo state miner's stake in the Kipoi copper mine for $111 million, taking full control of the mine, the Australian company said on Thursday. [ID:nL3N0QY2K0]  ** SNS Reaal, the Dutch financial services group nationalised last year, said international and domestic parties had expressed interest in its insurance operations which will go up for sale in September. [ID:nL5N0QY1CS]  **  Singapore sovereign fund GIC said on Thursday it has invested $104 mln in Taiwanese music streaming service provider KKBOX. [ID:nL3N0QY16T]  **  Intrepid Mines <IAU.AX> launched a friendly A$58.6 million ($54.7 million) all-share offer on Thursday for Blackthorn Resources <BTR.AX>, which plans to build a copper mine in Zambia, and announced a A$110 million share buy back. [ID:nL3N0QX2IV]